<TITLE>BoxLimit Task</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>

<H1><img src="moose6.gif"> <center>The Box Limit Task</center></H1>

<H2>Description</H2>
This task fires its event flag when the NAV_X NAV_Y or NAV_DEPTH variables are outside 
acceptable ranges for more than a specified length of time.


<H2>Publishes</H2>
<ul>
	<li>EndFlags
	<li>EventFlags
</ul>
<p>


<H2>Subscribes</H2>
<ul>
	<li><b>StartFlags</b>
	<li><b>NAV_X</b>
	<li><b>NAV_Y</b>
	<li><b>NAV_DEPTH</b>
</ul>
<p>

<H2>Configuration Block</H2>
<ul>



	<li><a href="CommonMOOSTask.html"> Common Task Parameters</a>
	<p>

	<li><H3>XMax,XMin,YMax,YMin,DepthMax</H3>
	<ul>
		<li><b>Syntax:	</b> XMax/XMin/YMax/YMin = Val (m)
		<li><b>Meaning:	</b> The Maximum or minum permissible working area for the vehicle XY and depth
		<li><b>Example:	</b> <i>XMax = 500</i> NAV_X must be less than 500m
	</ul>
	<p>
	
	<li><H3>IgnoreTime</H3>
	<ul>
		<li><b>Syntax:	</b> 	IgnoreTime = Time (s)
		<li><b>Meaning:	</b>	Set time after which a continous NAV* output exceeding a limit will cause the event flags to fire.
		<li><b>Example:	</b> <i>	IgnoreTime = 10 </i> Fire after a 10 second work area breech.
	</ul>
	<p>

</ul>

<H2>Example Block</H2>
<pre>
Task = LimitBox
{
	Name = LimitBox
	Priority = 0
	InitialState = ON
	TimeOut = NEVER
	EventFlag = EndMission

	XMax = 30
	XMin = -30
	YMax = 30
	YMin = -30
	DepthMax = 10
}
</pre>

